1
00:01:11,655 --> 00:01:13,065
你没被跟踪?
You weren't followed?

2
00:01:13,991 --> 00:01:15,447
没有
No.

3
00:01:15,576 --> 00:01:17,407
还是进来吧
Better come in.

4
00:01:21,832 --> 00:01:24,619
吉姆 别信任任何人
Trust no one, Jim.

5
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,787
尤其是大人物
Especially not in the mainstream.

6
00:01:32,217 --> 00:01:33,753
坐吧
Sit down.

7
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:50,266
我知道你还有一个匈牙利的身份可用
I understand you still have one H ungarian identity running?

8
00:01:52,279 --> 00:01:53,815
是的
I do.

9
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:02,323
我想派你去布达佩斯
I want you to go to Budapest.

10
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:07,412
这是秘密任务
'This is not above board.

11
00:02:07,544 --> 00:02:09,626
没有其他人知道
'Nobody else knows.

12
00:02:11,465 --> 00:02:13,672
他们要取我的命 吉姆老弟
'They're after my head, Jim boy.

13
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:17,088
你明白吗?
'Do you understand?

14
00:02:40,786 --> 00:02:43,823
我得到一个情报
'I have had an offer of service.

15
00:02:45,957 --> 00:02:49,495
一个匈牙利的将军
'A Hungarian general wants to come over.

16
00:02:50,837 --> 00:02:52,953
我想让你跟他碰面
'I would lik e you to meet him.'

17
00:02:56,051 --> 00:02:59,339
他有我想要的信息 吉姆
He has some information that I need, J im.

18
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,506
什么信息?
What information?

19
00:03:05,352 --> 00:03:06,967
宝藏
Treasure.

20
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,685
他知道苏联人安插在英国情报机关的内线的名字
'He has the name of the mole

21
00:03:12,818 --> 00:03:16,481
'the Russians have planted in the British intelligence service

22
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:19,525
他们都是圆场高层 （圆场：英国情报机构的代称，位于剑桥圆场）
'right at the top of the Circus.

23
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:28,243
这些烂苹果 吉姆
'There's a rotten apple, Jim.

24
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,536
我们要把他找出来
'We have to find it.'

25
00:03:34,837 --> 00:03:37,653
来点炖杂肉吧？尝过这个没？

26
00:03:38,175 --> 00:03:39,218
是的，我尝过

27
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:44,224
这东西很好，比炖牛肉要强 但是你现在在布达佩斯吃不到了

28
00:03:44,329 --> 00:03:45,059
为什么？

29
00:03:46,311 --> 00:03:48,109
因为那些猪都去莫斯科了

30
00:04:30,106 --> 00:04:32,817
我何时能见到你的朋友？

31
00:04:33,235 --> 00:04:35,008
你会见到的，不吃点吗？

32
00:05:12,859 --> 00:05:13,694
容我失陪一下

33
00:05:22,072 --> 00:05:23,812
住手!
Stop!

34
00:05:23,947 --> 00:05:24,989
谁让你开枪的？

35
00:05:25,061 --> 00:05:26,450
谁他妈的让你开枪的？

36
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:39,642
你会为我做见证吗?
Would you witness this for me?

37
00:06:39,774 --> 00:06:42,436
我希望能做得更多 老总
I wish I could done more, Control.

38
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:45,151
你已经尽力了 潘西
You did all you could, Percy.

39
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:53,986
哎 一个人应该知道什么时候退场
Well, a man should know when to leave the party.

40
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:59,328
史迈利呢?
What about Smiley?

41
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,623
史迈利和我一起走
Smiley is leaving with me.

42
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:26,233
你这个滑头 伊斯特哈斯
You little prick, Esterhase.

43
00:08:00,029 --> 00:08:05,294
《锅匠 裁缝 士兵 间谍》

44
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,161
各位 我们可以开始了吗?
Gentlemen, shall we start?

45
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:54,054
副部长拉康已经在等您了 潘西先生
U nder Secretary Lacon is ready for you, Sir Percy.

46
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:00,602
财政部不懂
The Treasury don't understand.

47
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:03,946
为什么情报局不能直接申请
Why can't the intelligence service simply put in a request

48
00:13:04,075 --> 00:13:05,656
普通的增拨资金
for a general increase in funding

49
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:08,697
那不就可以支持你们的特殊任务了吗?
and then you account for the spend on your special operation?

50
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:12,576
“巫术行动”需要保密
Operation Witchcraft needs to remain secret.

51
00:13:12,709 --> 00:13:15,667
-它有自己的一套 -这正是我们担心的
- It's a fiefdom of its own. - Yes, that's what's worrying us.

52
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:18,411
这整一件事让人摸不着头脑 不是吗?
The whole thing's very unaccountable, isn't it?

53
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:23,754
这个房子在伦敦哪儿大家都不知道
And this London house that nobody knows the address of,

54
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:25,501
真的有这个需要吗?
is that really necessary?

55
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:29,005
绝对有必要 要保护我们在苏联的线人
Now more than ever. We need to protect our Soviet source.

56
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:32,851
你要我们在哪里跟他碰面? 咖啡店吗?
So where do you propose we meet? In a caf?

57
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:35,686
这房子的租金和花费差不多是平常的两倍
The rent and rates on this house have doubled.

58
00:13:37,108 --> 00:13:39,895
在核武上就花了好几百万
We spent millions on nuclear warheads.

59
00:13:40,028 --> 00:13:42,895
我们不过要几千块租个房子
We're asking for a few thousand for a house.

60
00:13:43,031 --> 00:13:45,022
我好奇卡拉在克里姆林宫里 （卡拉：苏联情报机构头目）
I wonder if Karla has the same problem

61
00:13:45,158 --> 00:13:46,864
是不是有着同样的烦恼
with the Treasury at the Kremlin.

62
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:48,529
听好 没有人低估
Look, nobody underestimates

63
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:51,277
你们工作的重要性
the importance of the job you chaps are doing.

64
00:13:51,414 --> 00:13:53,700
但去年在布达佩斯发生的事
But what happened in Budapest last year,

65
00:13:55,752 --> 00:13:57,583
那简直是一个灾难
that was a disaster.

66
00:13:57,712 --> 00:13:59,623
坦白说
With respect, sir,

67
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:02,793
被杀的人不是你们办公室里的公务员
it wasn't one of your civil servants that got killed, was it?

68
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:05,337
现在说的也不是战壕里的士兵
Now this isn't about soldiers in trenches any more.

69
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:07,711
-是我们在前线的... -罗埃!
- We're the front line now... - Roy!

70
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:11,260
25年以来 我们唯一一次可以走近卡拉
For 25 years we've been the only thing standing between them and Karla

71
00:14:11,392 --> 00:14:13,633
走近莫斯科 甚至走近了他妈的第三次世界大战
and Moscow and the third bloody world war.

72
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:18,938
听好了 大臣非常满意你们目前的成果
Look, the Minister's very pleased with your progress so far.

73
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:22,733
不过 他对你们
He's less pleased, though,

74
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:25,478
跟美国人缺少协作这点不甚满意
with the lack of progress with our American cousins.

75
00:14:27,158 --> 00:14:28,568
你看
You see,

76
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:30,737
在他们的眼里
in their eyes,

77
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:33,361
你们还是烂船一艘
you're still a leaky ship.

78
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:52,554
怎样?
Yes?

79
00:14:52,683 --> 00:14:55,720
电话有人找你 长官 像是急事
'Someone on the line for you, sir. Seems urgent. '

80
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:57,593
好的 把电话接进来
All right, well put him through.

81
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:02,766
-喂? -是副部长拉康吗?
- Hello? - 'Ls this U nder Secretary Lacon? '

82
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:04,267
是的
Yes.

83
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:06,611
我叫里基・塔尔
My name's Ricki Tarr.

84
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:10,068
-你想怎样? -我要见你
- 'What do you want? ' - I need to meet you.

85
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,740
如果你想确认我的身份 可以去找我在圆场里的上司
If you need to confirm who I am, you can talk to my boss at the Circus,

86
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:16,612
彼得・吉勒姆
Peter Guillam.

87
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:19,411
只能是吉勒姆 不能找别人
But only Guillam, no one else.

88
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,514
都处理掉了吗?
You got clearance for that?

89
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:38,510
我不负责在外面捉人
Well, I'm not bloody chaining it up outside.

90
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:41,308
我提醒你 这里也许已经不安全了 到处是刺客
Mind you, no better off in here with this bunch of bloody cut-throats.

91
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:43,978
连他们的牙齿里也藏着武器
They'd have the gold out of your teeth.

92
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:47,648
我比布兰德早一步瞅到一个新来的女孩 他见过她没?
Thought I'd pop in and catch a glimpse of the new girl before Bland gets to her.

93
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:51,113
啊 对 金发美女 贝琳达
Ah, yes. Belinda the blonde.

94
00:15:51,242 --> 00:15:53,324
-他见过她没? -他当然见过了
- Has he seen her yet? - Of course he has.

95
00:15:53,453 --> 00:15:55,114
今早一来到的这儿的头等大事
Came down first thing this morning.

96
00:15:55,246 --> 00:15:56,952
贝琳达
Belinda.

97
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:10,007
-彼得・吉勒姆 -喂 彼得 我是奥利弗
- Peter Guillam. - 'Hello, Peter, this is Oliver.

98
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:12,718
我打电话来问一下...
'Just ringing to find out...

99
00:16:12,847 --> 00:16:16,339
'So Winston Churchill saved your life, Edie.'

100
00:16:16,476 --> 00:16:19,058
'I was working in the kitchen, getting dinner ready.

101
00:16:19,187 --> 00:16:20,927
'And he was late, you see.'

102
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:23,429
- 'During a raid? ' - 'During a raid, you see.'

103
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:25,397
'He said, "Why aren't you in that shelter?"'

104
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:27,062
- 'Why weren't you? ' - 'Well, because... '

105
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:40,663
老总的事 我很遗憾 史迈利先生
I was sorry to hear about Control, Mr Smiley.

106
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,924
他说塔尔从电话亭打电话给他
'He said Tarr called him from a phone box.'

107
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:07,773
他说有只地鼠
He said there's a mole,

108
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:12,194
潜伏在圆场的高层
right at the top of the Circus,

109
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:15,986
已经好几年了
that he's been there for years.

110
00:17:36,681 --> 00:17:38,296
这就意味着
It does mean

111
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:41,424
你现在相当适合帮我们调查这件事
you're rather well placed to look into this matter for us now,

112
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:43,597
不是吗?
doesn't it?

113
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:46,387
作为一个局外人
Outside the family.

114
00:17:55,825 --> 00:17:57,941
我已经退休了 奥利弗
I'm retired, Oliver.

115
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:00,284
你炒了我
You fired me.

116
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:02,278
事实上
The thing is,

117
00:18:02,415 --> 00:18:04,326
之前老总还在的时候
some time ago before Control died,

118
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,040
他跟我提过类似的想法
he came to me with a similar suggestion.

119
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:10,415
圆场有地鼠
That there is a mole.

120
00:18:13,593 --> 00:18:15,709
他没有跟你提起过他的猜疑吗?
He never mentioned his suspicions to you?

121
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:19,132
没有
No.

122
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:22,883
我只是以为.... 你是他的人
Oh, I just thought that as you were his man, so to speak...

123
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:25,351
你怎么回应他的?
What did you say to him?

124
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:28,266
我当时以为他犯了偏执病
I'm afraid I thought his paranoia had rather gotten the better of him

125
00:18:28,399 --> 00:18:31,357
打算自己拆自己的台
and he was going to pull his whole house down.

126
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:33,601
还有布达佩斯那个烂摊子
That bloody mess in Budapest.

127
00:18:38,034 --> 00:18:39,990
去他的 乔治
Damn it, George.

128
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,201
这是你的时代 你的辉煌
It's your generation, your legacy.

129
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:46,990
我应该想到的 如果这属实的话 你会想...
I would have thought, if there's any truth in it, you'd want to...

130
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,068
彼得留下给我用吧
I'll k eep Peter.

131
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:24,827
还有那个退休警察 孟德尔
And there's a retired Special Branch man, Mendel.

132
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:28,080
我也要
I should lik e to have him.

133
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:32,494
- Lift up.

134
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:38,503
And quickly down again.

135
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:46,014
我知道有个地方 在利物浦街附近的一家小旅馆
There's a place I know, sir. A little hotel near Liverpool Street.

136
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:24,171
请小心点　这是乔治王朝风格的
Be careful with it. Please. It's Georgian.

137
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:28,094
我朋友需要一个安静的工作环境 蒲波-格雷汉姆太太
My friend wants peace and quiet in order to work, Mrs Pope Graham.

138
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,342
没有干扰的环境
No disturbances.

139
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:32,811
她的真名只有格雷汉姆
Her real name is just Graham.

140
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:35,056
加上“蒲波”是为了表示等级
Added the Pope for a touch of class.

141
00:20:49,582 --> 00:20:53,871
彼得 你能拿到老总公寓的钥匙吗?
'Peter, did you get the k eys to Control's flat? '

142
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:05,629
# And did those feet in ancient time

143
00:21:05,765 --> 00:21:10,008
# Walk upon England's mountains green #

144
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:13,811
噢!
Oh!

145
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:43,104
乔治!
'George! '

146
00:22:45,155 --> 00:22:46,565
乔治! 给我进来!
George, get in here!

147
00:22:50,953 --> 00:22:52,864
乔治
George.

148
00:22:54,373 --> 00:22:56,580
坐下
Sit down.

149
00:23:01,922 --> 00:23:04,083
看看这份不知所谓的东西
Tak e a look at this nonsense.

150
00:23:09,138 --> 00:23:10,594
这是苏联最高指挥部
Report by Soviet high command

151
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:14,591
就近期他们在黑海的海军演习发回的报告
on their recent naval exercises in the Black Sea.

152
00:23:14,727 --> 00:23:17,389
这正是海军部向我们
Just what the admiralty has been begging us

153
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:19,227
乞求的情报
for some information on.

154
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:22,606
-你从哪里搞到的? -不是我搞来的
- Where did you get this? - I didn't.

155
00:23:22,735 --> 00:23:24,600
不是我 是潘西和他的小团伙拿来的
Percy and his little cabal walk ed in with it.

156
00:23:24,737 --> 00:23:26,819
-老总 这... -闭嘴
- Look, Control... - Shut up.

157
00:23:27,698 --> 00:23:29,984
文风差得令人发指
Style appalling.

158
00:23:30,117 --> 00:23:33,109
明显是彻头彻尾地瞎编乱作
Patently a fabrication from beginning to end.

159
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:37,363
-不过倒像是真的 -如果内容属实就等于挖到了金矿
- Just could be the real thing. - Well, if it's genuine, it's gold dust.

160
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:41,208
但这个话题总是惹人猜疑
But its topicality mak es it suspect.

161
00:23:41,337 --> 00:23:44,625
史迈利生性多疑 潘西
Smiley is suspicious, Percy.

162
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:47,590
从哪儿弄来的? 通过什么渠道得来?
Where did it come from? What's the access?

163
00:23:47,718 --> 00:23:49,709
我的一个新线人
A new secret source of mine.

164
00:23:49,845 --> 00:23:51,506
可是他怎么可能弄到…?
But how could he possibly have access?

165
00:23:51,639 --> 00:23:54,802
他连最高决策层的机密都有办法搞到
He has access to the most sensitive levels of policy-making.

166
00:23:56,727 --> 00:23:58,308
我们把这个情报源称之为“巫术”
We've named the operation Witchcraft.

167
00:23:58,437 --> 00:24:01,395
史迈利 潘西和他的搭档们已经绕过了我们
Oh, Percy and his pals bypassed us, Smiley.

168
00:24:01,523 --> 00:24:03,684
直接去找部长了
Gone straight to the minister.

169
00:24:03,817 --> 00:24:08,106
潘西可以对他新伙计的身份
Percy has been allowed to k eep the identity of his new friend

170
00:24:08,238 --> 00:24:09,648
绝对保密
top secret.

171
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:13,400
部长与我一致认为这里充斥了太多不清不楚的事情
The minister agrees too many secrets are blown around here.

172
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:15,446
接二连三的失败 数不清的丑闻
Too much failure, too many scandals.

173
00:24:15,579 --> 00:24:18,912
-可靠的情报却少得可怜 -潘西说到点子上了 老总
- Too little solid intelligence. - Percy does have a point, Control.

174
00:24:19,041 --> 00:24:21,657
我们该对抗的是共产主义 而不是自己人
We should be fighting Communism, not each other.

175
00:24:21,794 --> 00:24:24,501
这些争斗毁了我们的名声 也让我们失去了同盟伙伴...
Meanwhile we're losing our reputation, our partners.

176
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,961
你们这些恶毒的美国佬!
Your bloody Yank s!

